menu "libtracer"

    config LIBTRACER_VERTEX_LOCK_STRIPES
        int "Vertex lock-stripe count"
        range 1 256
        default 16
        help
            Number of process-wide mutex/condvar lock stripes shared by every
            graph vertex (libtracer #361 section 2). This is the ONLY global
            mutable buffer libtracer links into a node: N stripes cost N lazily
            allocated FreeRTOS mutexes (~90 B of heap each) plus N condition
            variables, paid once a graph_t exists — independent of how many
            vertices you register.

            The stripe a vertex rides is chosen by hashing its pinned address,
            so lowering the count only raises CONTROL-PLANE lock contention
            (ring trim, edge/ACL mutation, await wake); the lock-free LKV
            read/write hot path is unaffected. On a single-core chip target a
            small count (4-8) reclaims RAM at negligible contention cost; the
            host/multi-core default stays 16.

            The core header (<libtracer/vertex.hpp>) already honors a
            -DLIBTRACER_VERTEX_LOCK_STRIPES override; this option is the ESP-IDF
            front door for it. The component propagates the value as a PUBLIC
            compile definition so every translation unit that includes
            <libtracer/vertex.hpp> agrees: the stripe table is an
            `inline constinit` object, and a size mismatch across TUs is an ODR
            violation.

endmenu
